{"TopicDetails": {"type": 0, "ccm2Id": 44835052, "cftId": 0, "identifier": "EP-COMM-SUBV-2022-EYY", "title": "European Year of Youth grants", "publicationDateLong": 1648080000000, "callIdentifier": "EP-COMM-SUBV-2022-EYY", "callTitle": "European Year of Youth grants", "callccm2Id": 44835060, "allowPartnerSearch": true, "frameworkProgramme": {"id": 43697167, "abbreviation": "EP", "description": "European Parliament"}, "programmeDivision": [{"id": 43697187, "abbreviation": "EP-1-1", "description": "Grants in the Area of Communication"}], "topicMGAs": [], "sme": false, "actions": [{"status": {"id": 31094503, "abbreviation": "Closed", "description": "Closed"}, "types": [{"typeOfAction": "EP-PJG EP Project Grants", "typeOfMGA": [{"id": 43694065, "abbreviation": "EP-AG", "description": "EP Action Grant Budget-Based"}]}], "plannedOpeningDate": "24 March 2022", "submissionProcedure": {"id": 31094504, "abbreviation": "single-stage", "description": "single-stage"}, "deadlineDates": ["11 May 2022"]}], "latestInfos": [], "budgetOverviewJSONItem": {"budgetTopicActionMap": {"3385464": [{"action": "EP-COMM-SUBV-2022-EYY - EP-PJG EP Project Grants", "plannedOpeningDate": "24 March 2022", "deadlineModel": "single-stage", "deadlineDates": ["11 May 2022"], "budgetYearMap": {"2022": 1000000}, "budgetTopicActionMap": {}}]}, "budgetYearsColumns": ["2022"]}, "description": "<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">ExpectedOutcome</SPAN>:<p>The expected results of the actions financed under this call are:</p><ul level=\"0\"><li>An increased awareness among young European citizens about the action of the European Union and its institutions, in particular the European Parliament;</li><li>The establishment of pan-European participatory channels, connecting the European Parliament with the younger citizens and encouraging their active participation in together.eu<sup><a target=_self href=#fn1 id=r1>[1]</a></sup>, the platform of the European Parliament;</li><li>An increased engagement of young European citizens with the construction of a vibrant European democracy, thus encouraging their active involvement and participation in the European Elections 2024 communication campaign.</li> </ul>\n<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">Objective</SPAN>:<p>The principal objective of the call is to encourage and to facilitate the active engagement of European young citizens with the construction of a vibrant European democracy keeping particularly in mind their participation in the European Elections 2024. The European Parliament is looking to co-finance projects articulating a coherent, consistent and cost efficient work programme encompassing two types of actions:</p><ul level=\"0\"><li>The first action consist in creating pan-European networks of advocates for democratic participation, by selecting young people to be trained. Each network of advocates should cover at least seven European Union Member States. The applicant has to detail in the project proposal the choice of countries that they have made as well as the process of identification and selection of young advocates forming the new pan-European networks.</li><li>The second action consists in design and implementation of capacity building through training, aiming at providing the young advocates with skills, competences and tools to play an active role in the democratic life and in the promotion of the democratic values, including the participation in the European Elections in 2024.</li> </ul>\n<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">Scope</SPAN>:na\n<p id=fn1><a  target=_self href=#r1>[1]</a></p>", "conditions": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;color:#404040;&#10;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">Conditions</span></b><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;color:#404040;&#10;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n<p><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color:#404040;mso-themecolor:&#10;text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">1.&nbsp;</span></b><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">Admissibility conditions: </span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">described in section 5 of the call document</span>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">Proposal page limits and layout:</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:&#10;EN-US\"> described in Part B of the Application Form available in the Submission System<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">2. Eligible countries: </span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">described in section 6 of the call document<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">3. Other eligibility conditions:</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\"> described in section 6 of the call document<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n<p><b>4. Financial and operational capacity and exclusion: </b><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:bold\">described in </span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">section 7 of the call document</span><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:bold\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n<p><b><span lang=\"FR-BE\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:FR-BE\">5.&nbsp;Evaluation and award:</span></b><span lang=\"FR-BE\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:FR-BE\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n<ul>\r\n    <li>&nbsp;<b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;&#10;     mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">Submission and evaluation processes</span></b><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">:</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\"> described <span style=\"color:#404040;&#10;     mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191\">section 8 of the call document and      the</span> </span><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/common/guidance/om_en.pdf\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">Online Manual</span></a><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n</ul>\n<ul>\r\n    <li>&nbsp;<b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">Award criteria, scoring and      thresholds:</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">      described in section 9 of the call document<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n</ul>\n<p><span id=\"1617195973454S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"1617195972667S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">Indicative timeline for      evaluation and grant agreement: </span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold\">described in      section 4 of the call document<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n</ul>\n<p><b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-ansi-language:&#10;EN-US\">6</span></b><b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">. Legal and financial set-up of the grants: </span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">described <span style=\"color:#404040;&#10;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191\">in section 10 of the call document</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\"><span style=\"color:#404040;&#10;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\n<p><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:&#10;11.0pt;line-height:115%;color:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;&#10;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">Documents<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">Call documents:</span></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: 